    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Using an audio recorder, you can:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Record until the user stops the recording"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Record for a specified duration"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Pause and resume a recording"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Obtain input audio-level data that you can use to provide level metering"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In iOS, the audio being recorded comes from the device connected by the user—built-in microphone or headset microphone, for example. In macOS, the audio comes from the system’s default audio input device as set by a user in System Preferences."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can implement a delegate object for an audio recorder to respond to audio interruptions and audio decoding errors, and to the completion of a recording."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To configure a recording, including options such as bit depth, bit rate, and sample rate conversion quality, configure the audio recorder’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avaudiorecorder/1390903-settings"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " dictionary. Use the settings keys described in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avaudiorecorder#2888050"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To configure an appropriate audio session for recording, refer to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avaudiosession"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avaudiosessiondelegate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "AVAudioRecorder"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class is intended to allow you to make audio recordings with very little programming overhead. Other classes that can be used for recording audio in iOS and macOS include "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureaudiodataoutput"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and the Audio Queue services described in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Audio Queue Services Programming Guide",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/MusicAudio/Conceptual/AudioQueueProgrammingGuide/Introduction/Introduction.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40005343"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In macOS, you can also use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avcaptureaudiofileoutput"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class to record audio."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
